---
title: Turkish-Spiced Chickpea Couscous Bowls with Spinach, Tomato & Lemony Yogurt Sauce
description: While we love chickpeas no matter how they come, our number-one fave way to eat them is crisp-roasted. And here, they’re the star of this hearty, colorful bowl. You’ll coat them in our savory Turkish-inspired spice blend, then pop them in a hot oven until they’re—what? Crispy! You’ll spoon the chickpeas over a bowl of tender, garlicky couscous strewn with wilted spinach, fresh tomatoes, and a squeeze of lemon. Drizzle as much tangy, lemony yogurt sauce as you like on top for a bright pop. It’s a vegetarian dinner idea we just knew you’d love.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/turkish-spiced-chickpea-couscous-bowls-b370b059.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/turkish-spiced-chickpea-couscous-bowls-645a6a846dcbce11db0ed092-4ce653f9.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkish-spiced-chickpea-couscous-bowls-645a6a846dcbce11db0ed092
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
